 ADVENT (ad'vent) n. The prototypical computer adventure game, first
implemented on the PDP-10 by MIT hackers Dave Lebling, Mark Blank and Don R.
Woods as a demo for a natural-language parser they were hacking on at the
time. Now better known as Adventure, but the TOPS-10 operating system only
permitted 6-letter filenames. "A huge green fierce snake bars the way!"